pstronga href=http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/buddypress/Download 1.6.4/a now or visit Dashboard → Updates in your site admin to update now./strong/p";}i:37;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:68:"Ping-O-Matic: Engage: Make Your Online Home a Place for Conversation";s:4:"guid";s:32:"http://blog.pingomatic.com/?p=77";s:4:"link";s:49:"http://blog.pingomatic.com/2013/01/24/engagement/";s:11:"description";s:2639:"pa href=http://pingomatic.com/Ping-O-Matic/a is all about getting your latest content out into the world and driving more traffic to your blog. And if you have a blog, chances are you want to be part of a larger community. You don#8217;t just want to create and share your stuff #8212; you want to connect with people who share your interests and passions in a meaningful way./p
pPublishing a post is just one step in blogging #8212; getting people to engage with you is another. How do you start a conversation?/p
h3Here are some tips:/h3
ul
listrongEnd with a prompt./strong At the end of a post, encourage comments by asking a specific question or two, which is a better way of generating feedback than more general #8220;Leave a comment#8221; or #8220;What do you think?#8221; prompts. Your blog isn’t just a monologue #8212; you want to open up the discussion to others./li
listrongReply to comments./strong Your job doesn’t end when you hit publish. When readers leave comments, keep the conversation going with a thoughtful reply./li
listrongBut don’t reply to every comment./strong If you receive many comments and reply to each with a generic one-liner (#8220;Thanks!#8221;), your comment thread won#8217;t be interesting. Feel free to reply to first-time visitors to welcome them to your site, but in general, reply only if you have something substantial to add to the existing conversation./li
listrongModerate with care./strong It’s best not to encourage or allow nasty and abusive comments. They intimidate new readers, derail conversations, and distract you from good blogging. It#8217;s emyour/em online home #8212; don#8217;t be afraid to give polite warnings to visitors who aren#8217;t appropriate./li
listrongPost commenting guidelines./strong If you find yourself doing a lot of policing, one way to be transparent about the type of comments you will and will not permit is to post simple guidelines. This can help you attract the kind of commenters you want, and deter unwanted behavior./li
listrongReturn the visit./strong Developing friendships with your readers is one of the best parts of blogging. If you have loyal commenters, make sure you visit and engage on their blogs, too. If they like what you post, chances are you’ll be into their stuff as well./li
/ul
